# Azure — Arquitectura objetivo

## Servicios

| Capa | Servicio Azure | Propósito |
|------|----------------|-----------|
| API | **Container Apps** | FastAPI + agentes + LangGraph |
| Web | **Static Web Apps** | React (Vite build) |
| LLM | **Azure OpenAI** | GPT-4o + embeddings |
| RAG | **Azure AI Search** | Índice vectorial de políticas |
| DB | **Cosmos DB for MongoDB** | Audit trail + HITL + evaluaciones |
| Secretos | **Key Vault** | Keys OpenAI, Mongo, Search |
| Logs | **Application Insights** | Trazas y métricas |
| Registry | **ACR** | Imagen Docker backend |
| IaC | **Bicep** en `infra/` | Todo como código |

## Topología

```
Static Web Apps (React) ──▶ Container Apps (FastAPI)
                                  ├── Azure OpenAI
                                  ├── AI Search (RAG)
                                  ├── Cosmos DB (MongoDB API)
                                  └── Key Vault
                         Application Insights ◀── logs
```

## Estructura `infra/modules/`

`container-app`, `static-web-app`, `cosmos-mongodb`, `key-vault`, `ai-search`, `app-insights`, `container-registry`

## Variables Container Apps

```
MONGODB_URI                   # secret ref — Cosmos DB connection string
AZURE_OPENAI_*                # secret refs
AZURE_SEARCH_*                # secret refs
APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING
CORS_ORIGINS
```

## Local vs Azure

| Componente | Local | Azure |
|------------|-------|-------|
| DB | MongoDB Docker :27017 | Cosmos DB MongoDB API |
| RAG | Chroma | AI Search |
| LLM | Azure OpenAI | Azure OpenAI |

## Justificación README

Cosmos DB MongoDB: documentos anidados para audit trail; servicio gestionado Azure; compatible con Motor/PyMongo local.
